7 A Concurrent Resolution recognizing the OKC Spark
professional softball team and their contributions to
8 professional sports in Oklahoma; praising the OKC
Spark’s participation in the Athletes Unlimited
9 Softball League (AUSL); recognizing Oklahoma City’s
designation as host for softball during the 2028
10 Olympic Games; and directing distribution.
11
12
13 WHEREAS, the Oklahoma Legislature is proud to recognize the OKC
14 Spark professional softball team and founder and executive director
15 Tina Floyd for the team’s exceptional contributions to the landscape
16 of professional sports in the State of Oklahoma; and
17 WHEREAS, the Spark’s success is anchored by the leadership of
18 General Manager Kirk Walker and Head Coach Amber Flores, whose
19 expertise and dedication have built a culture of excellence that
20 resonates both on the field and throughout the community; and
21 WHEREAS, the team is further distinguished by the remarkable
22 talent of standout athletes like Kinzie Hansen and Sydney Sherrill,
23 whose collegiate legacies and professional achievements continue to
24 inspire young Oklahomans and elevate the caliber of the game; and
ENGR. S. C. R. NO. 21 Page 1

1 WHEREAS, the OKC Spark’s participation in the Athletes Unlimited
2 Softball League (AUSL) represents a bold new chapter for women’s
3 athletics, providing a professional framework that ensures the long-
4 term sustainability and growth of the sport; and
5 WHEREAS, the advancement of women’s professional sports is vital
6 to the growth and diversification of Oklahoma’s sports economy,
7 fostering innovation, job creation, and increased tourism within the
8 Oklahoma City metropolitan area; and
9 WHEREAS, the international sporting community has recognized the
10 premier facilities and passionate culture of Oklahoma City,
11 designating it as the host for softball during the 2028 Olympic
12 Games; and
13 WHEREAS, the Olympic softball team will be led by Oklahoma’s own
14 Patty Gasso, whose historic leadership and championship pedigree
15 further solidify our state’s status as the global epicenter of the
16 sport; and
17 WHEREAS, the visionary leadership of Tina Floyd and the
18 collective brilliance of the Spark organization have been
19 instrumental in preparing Oklahoma to welcome the world stage,
20 ensuring that the legacy of softball continues to thrive and impact
21 our economy for years to come.
22 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE 2ND SESSION
23 OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE, THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
24 CONCURRING THEREIN:
ENGR. S. C. R. NO. 21 Page 2

1 THAT the Oklahoma Legislature recognizes the OKC Spark for their
2 tremendous success, their contributions to the landscape of
3 professional sports in Oklahoma, their participation in AUSL, and
4 the advancement of women’s professional sports and its multiple
5 benefits to the state.
6 THAT the Oklahoma Legislature applauds Oklahoma City’s
7 designation as host for softball during the 2028 Olympic Games and
8 the role of Tina Floyd and the Spark organization in bringing the
9 sport and the State of Oklahoma national and international
10 attention.
11 THAT a copy of this concurrent resolution be distributed to the
12 OKC Spark and the AUSL.
13 Adopted by the Senate the 16th day of April, 2026.
